        "id": 5140
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-03T21:13:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I know this already exists, but it\u0027s super confusing as a name since the type has nothing to do with a codepoint, it is a reference made up of indices and lengths into other arrays, at best it\u0027s CodepointRepresentation? fCodePoints is kinda ok since the idea is that there is one entry per codepoint.",
