    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b1747477_cd8fa7f3",
        "filename": "modules/skparagraph/src/ParagraphImpl.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 304,
      "author": {
        "id": 5140
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-03T21:13:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I suppose it works to put this here, but it\u0027s a bit arbitrary (it works because shapeTextIntoEndlessLine happens to call it before doing other things). It might make more sense to put it there with a comment that shapeTextIntoEndlessLine is the thing that calls all of the icu dependencies (and if it isn\u0027t, then it should be put somewhere else).",
      "revId": "66ce4836364071ffe67dd549b907bb92c5fe0896",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "cda31a14_05f2ae9a",
        "filename": "modules/skparagraph/src/ParagraphImpl.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 955,
      "author": {
        "id": 5140
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-03T21:13:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is kinda awkward due to kWhiteSpace, which it doesn\u0027t work with. It works on \u0027Before\u0027 type things. It\u0027s also only used in one place and seems to use a potentially expensive std::function. Does this really need to be this generic?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 955,
        "startChar": 20,
        "endLine": 955,
        "endChar": 42
      },
      "revId": "66ce4836364071ffe67dd549b907bb92c5fe0896",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e44ad30a_0f477091",
        "filename": "modules/skparagraph/src/ParagraphImpl.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 955,
      "author": {
        "id": 5140
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-03T21:13:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is confusingly an \u0027if any selected flags\u0027 and not \u0027if all selected flags\u0027. In practice I don\u0027t se any reason to want to mix two flags? This should just take the enum type and expect only one flag.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 955,
        "startChar": 43,
        "endLine": 955,
        "endChar": 65
      },
      "revId": "66ce4836364071ffe67dd549b907bb92c5fe0896",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
